\par\plain {\f1\fs22\b1\i0 Introduction}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Jesus seems to be preparing us for a revival of his message. During the last fifty years we have been given two publications that seem to point to preparations for a revival. There are probably other publications but the following two publications are the focus of this book. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 The Urantia Book was first published in 1955. It is broken down into four sections. The first three sections contain incredible details of the universe we live in while the fourth section gives an eyewitness account by celestial beings of the life of Jesus from birth to death and resurrection. The Urantia book was approved by Jesus for publication for our time. None of the information in the Urantia book was dictated by Jesus himself but was written by various personalities under his celestial administration. I believe this is important to acknowledge because of the nature of people to dogmatize every word coming from Jesus himself. The authors do however quote Jesus words directly as they witnessed them.  Jesus let his bestowal story be told by those humans who witnessed his life in the flesh as recorded in the Bible. Jesus also let his celestial personalities write the Urantia Book from their vantage point. Jesus did not personally write the Urantia book just as he did not personally write the Bible. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 The second publication I want to mention is the Course in Miracles. It was published In 1973. Notation was taken down by the scribe Helen Schuman over a seven year period. Helen claims to have detected a voice in her mind that instructed her to write the Course in Miracles. Again, I think it is important to notice the method Jesus used to communicate the information. Through Helens notes we can see how the information was written down and edited many times. These versions are referred to online as the urtext. The notes Helen took were edited by her and Bill T over many years. Again, we see a similar pattern to Jesus technique. He never writes anything down himself. Helen confessed that she constantly fought the urge to edit the course often as she was taking shorthand notes. While it is dictated by Jesus, it is not a perfect word for word dictation. We must assume because of her confession of fighting the urge to edit, she may have even edited the first set of shorthand notes. We will never know for sure. A comment in the original notes mentions Helen as a scribe. This comment leads me to believe Helen did the best she could but may have inserted some of her own thoughts into the process.  }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 ACIM notes comment:"NOTE: Scribes have a particular role in the Plan of Atonement, because they have the ability to EXPERIENCE revelations themselves, and also to put into words enough of the experience to serve as a basis for miracles."\line }
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 The Urantia Book is about creating a balanced personality between our divine and human selves to eventually fuse them together as one. A Course in Miracles is the curriculum to deprogram the ego from the error inherent on a confused planet, train your mind to think from a place of pure sincerity so you learn to communicate with your divine self until there is no difference between your mind (thoughts) and God's mind and your desire to do God's will fuses you with your thought adjuster.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 For anyone interested in a deep dive of the notes Helen took, you can find them online by typing urtext and Course In Miracles. It is truly a fascinating and insightful process. I mention the process to bring attention to the imperfect nature of revelation. The UB does claim to be an unadulterated word for word publication as written by the celestial personalities mentioned at the end of each paper. Some also claim the CIM is a word for word dictation by Jesus. But the notes give caution to that idea. The process is insightful for another reason. Helen was not familiar with the UB. She was a catholic. I often wonder if Helen would have accepted the UB had she known about it. She had a herculean task to be a scribe for Jesus. How could Jesus possibly educate her on the UB and at the same time dictate the CIM to her? I doubt it was possible. In fact, it seems Jesus tried to stay within the Christian domain while attempting to relate Urantia concepts to her. Since Helen was unaware of the UB she was also unaware of the terms and ideas within the UB. While concepts may overlap they are not as obvious due to Jesus use of Helens existing vocabulary. As it was, Helen fought to understand what she was writing. The possibility that she could read the UB and take down dictation of the CIM is remote. Therefore we will need to pay attention to concepts written in slightly different terminology. Once this becomes obvious, the commonality between the two books becomes a little more obvious. (Concepts such as time, the fragment of God, miracles and their relation to time, what is the sonship)}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 One of the biggest gains I received from studying the Course is seeing the eternal perspective more clearly in the UB. If you consider the Course as Jesus perspective from the eternal present as abstract as it seems, you will notice the same perspective all throughout the UB. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Chapter One CIM.  }
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \line I do believe the Course in Miracles is a course in adjuster fusion. Anything short of fusion is still progress. If you assume fusion as the goal of the course the statement in the beginning of the book takes on a deeper meaning. (What is an adjuster? What is fusion?)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 \line \line ACIM 1 "This is a course in miracles. It is a required course. Only the time you take it is voluntary. Free will does not mean that you can establish the curriculum. It means only that you may elect what you want to take at a given time."}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \line \line Let's take a closer look. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \line \line "This is a course in miracles." Is fusion related to miracles? As we saw in Jesus life, miracles were unavoidable once he attained fusion status. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \line \line "It is a required course." Is fusion a requirement? If we want to attain paradise, then yes we must fuse. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \line \line "Only the time you take it is voluntary." Can we postpone fusion? Sure we can, on some worlds mortal fusion is common. For us, we will need mansion world training until some future time when it will be common to fuse from the mortal state. Perhaps the Course in Miracles is a step in that direction. (What is mansion world training)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \line \line "Free will does not mean that you can establish the curriculum. It means only that you may elect what you want to take at a given time." }
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 We can take the course now if we choose, but there is no guarantee that we will "establish" the goal of the course. We know what fusion looked like for Jesus by reading the Urantia book. If we set fusion as the goal, we then have an idea of what the outcome should look like. We will reach milestones on the journey for sure. But if we assign some lessor goal to the course outcome, we may think we have established the goal of the course when in reality we have only reached a milestone. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 ACIM }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 2}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  The course does not aim at teaching the meaning of love, for that is beyond what can be taught. It does aim, however, at removing the blocks to the awareness of love's presence, which is your natural inheritance. The opposite of love is fear, but what is all-encompassing can have no opposite.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The course does not aim at teaching the meaning of love, for that is beyond what can be taught.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 If we search the Urantia Book for a definition of love we see that it references the Thought Adjuster (a fragment of God living within us, the purest most indestructible form of reality) as the greatest manifestation of divine love. }{\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Since the Adjuster is the greatest manifestation of divine love, we can connect the dots and determine that love and the god fragment that lives within us is beyond our ability to understand. We can however, experience this infinite reality.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 UB 2:5.10 The greatest manifestation of the divine love for mortal beings is observed in the bestowal of the Thought Adjusters, but your greatest revelation of the Father's love is seen in the bestowal life of his Son Michael (Jesus) as he lived on earth the ideal spiritual life. It is the indwelling Adjuster who individualizes the love of God to each human soul.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It does aim, however, at removing the blocks to the awareness of love's presence, which is your natural inheritance.\u8221\'94 In Urantia Book terms I read this to mean the course aims at removing the blocks to the Thought Adjusters presence. This course is the result of the life Jesus lived in the flesh. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 UB (196:3.1) Personal, spiritual religious experience is an efficient solvent for most mortal difficulties; it is an effective sorter, evaluator, and adjuster of all human problems. Religion does not remove or destroy human troubles, but it does dissolve, absorb, illuminate, and transcend them. True religion unifies the personality for effective adjustment to all mortal requirements. Religious faith\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 THE POSITIVE LEADING OF THE INDWELLING DIVINE PRESENCE\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 unfailingly enables the God-knowing man to bridge that gulf existing between the intellectual logic which recognizes the Universal First Cause as It and those positive affirmations of the soul which aver this First Cause is He, the heavenly Father of Jesus' gospel, the personal God of human salvation.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The opposite of love is fear, but what is all-encompassing can have no opposite.\u8221\'94 The UB is full of quotes that mention the negative effects of fear.  }{\f2\fs18\b1\i0 UB }{\f3\fs18\b0\i0  }{\f3\fs18\b0\i0\cf4 (48:7.4)}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  2. Few persons live up to the faith which they really have. Unreasoned fear is a master intellectual fraud practiced upon the evolving mortal soul. }
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 ACIM }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 3}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  This course can therefore be summed up very simply in this way:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 ACIM }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 4}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  Nothing real can be threatened.\line \~\~\~Nothing unreal exists.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 ACIM }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 5}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  Herein lies the peace of God.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b0\i0 CIM 4 \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93Nothing real can be threatened.\u8221\'94 UB \u8220\'93Nothing of survival value is ever lost in all the wide universe.\u8221\'94 UB \u8220\'93Adjusters never fail; nothing worth surviving is ever lost; every meaningful value in every will creature is certain of survival, irrespective of the survival or nonsurvival of the meaning-discovering or evaluating personality.\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b0\i0 This statement must be considered from the eternal perspective. In the material world fear and love seem to exist side by side. Yet we find the above language in the UB that seems at odds with our understanding. Without getting too technical, the personality is eternal and unchanging per the UB. Our identity is what is at stake here in time. The adjuster survives, the personality attains deity with or without our identity per the UB. From the eternal perspective nothing is lost that had its roots in eternity.}
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b0\i0 CIM \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'93Nothing unreal exists.\u8221\'94 UB "much of your past life"\u8230\'85"and it's memories".... "will perish". Much of this life is considered an illusion by our celestial friends.}
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b0\i0 UB 112:5.22.The Thought Adjuster will recall and rehearse for you only those memories and experiences which are a part of, and essential to, your universe career. If the Adjuster has been a partner in the evolution of aught in the human mind, then will these worth-while experiences survive in the eternal consciousness of the Adjuster. But much of your past life and its memories, having neither spiritual meaning nor morontia value, will perish with the material brain; much of material experience will pass away as onetime scaffolding which, having bridged you over to the morontia level, no longer serves a purpose in the universe. But personality and the relationships between personalities are never scaffolding; mortal memory of personality relationships has cosmic value and will persist. On the mansion worlds you will know and be known, and more, you will remember, and be remembered by, your onetime associates in the short but intriguing life on Urantia.}
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f3\fs24\b0\i0 CIM \loch\af3\hich\af3\dbch\af3\uc1\u8220\'935 Herein lies the peace of God.\u8221\'94 UB (144:8.8) "It would appear that the Father in heaven has hidden some of these truths from the wise and haughty, while he has revealed them to babes. But the Father does all things well; the Father reveals himself to the universe by the methods of his own choosing. Come, therefore, all you who labor and are heavy laden, and you shall find rest for your souls. Take upon you the divine yoke, and you will experience the peace of God, which passes all understanding."}
\par\pard\plain \sa100\sb100\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs48\b1\i0 Chapter One: Introduction to Miracles}
\par\pard\plain \ql\ltrch\loch \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 I. Principles of Miracles}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 1.}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 1}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  There is no order of difficulty among miracles. One is not "harder" or "bigger" than another. They are all the same. All expressions of love are maximal.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 2. }{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 2}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  Miracles as such do not matter. The only thing that matters is their Source, Which is far beyond human evaluation.}
\par\plain \f3\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 CIM \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'931.}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\super 1}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0  There is no order of difficulty among miracles. One is not "harder" or "bigger" than another. They are all the same. All expressions of love are maximal.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 (146:2.7)}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 In several places the UB says that when we line up our will with Gods will all things are possible.   UB 131:10.2 With our heavenly Father all things are possible. Since he is the Creator, having made all things and all beings, it could not be otherwise. UB  \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93When you have become wholly dedicated to the doing of the will of the Father in heaven, the answer to all your petitions will be forthcoming because your prayers will be in full accordance with the Father's will, and the Father's will is ever manifest throughout his vast universe. WHAT THE TRUE SON DESIRES AND THE INFINITE FATHER WILLS IS. Such a prayer cannot remain unanswered, and no other sort of petition can possibly be fully answered.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 2. }{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 2}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  Miracles as such do not matter. The only thing that matters is their Source, Which is far beyond human evaluation.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 The source of miracles is the adjuster. In paper 136 Jesus made many decisions on how he would perform his public ministry. One decision was that he would not utilize the celestial hosts to perform super human feats. His adjuster assured him they would honor his wish except when it involved the fathers will. The fact that he was discussing how he would limit the use of  miracles with his adjuster means the adjuster is the source of miracles. And the adjuster is beyond human evaluation. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 136:5.4.In accepting this command of the universe hosts in attendance upon Christ Michael, the Personalized Adjuster took great pains to point out to Jesus that, while such an assembly of universe creatures could be limited in their space activities by the delegated authority of their Creator, such limitations were not operative in connection with their function in time.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 136:5.5 In order to prevent the appearance of apparent time miracles, it was necessary for Jesus to remain constantly time conscious. Any lapse of time consciousness on his part, in connection with the entertainment of definite desire, was equivalent to the enactment of the thing conceived in the mind of this Creator Son, and without the intervention of time.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 3. }{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\super\cb3\highlight3 3}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3  Miracles occur naturally as expressions of love. The real miracle is the love that inspires them. In this sense, everything that comes from love is a miracle.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 3. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Miracles occur naturally as expressions of love.\u8221\'94  One of the stories of healing in the UB is a great example of how miracles can occur naturally. In this case Jesus was totally unaware. UB (152:0.2) And when those who were near him denied that they had touched him, Peter spoke up: "Master, you can see that this crowd presses you, threatening to crush us, and yet you say 'someone has touched me.' What do you mean?" Then Jesus said: "I asked who touched me, for I perceived that living energy had gone forth from me." As Jesus looked about him, his eyes fell upon a near-by woman, who, coming forward, knelt at his feet and said: "For years I have been afflicted with a scourging hemorrhage. I have suffered many things from many physicians; I have spent all my substance, but none could cure me. Then I heard of you, and I thought if I may but touch the hem of his garment, I shall certainly be made whole. And so I pressed forward with the crowd as it moved along until, standing near you, Master, I touched the border of your garment, and I was made whole; I know that I have been healed of my affliction."}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb3\highlight3 CIM \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93The real miracle is the love that inspires them. In this sense, everything that comes from love is a miracle.}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 Again, the UB says the adjuster is the most divine affection in all creation which even the authors of the UB regard as miraculous. UB (110:0.2) As far as I am conversant with the affairs of a universe, I regard the love and devotion of a Thought Adjuster as the most truly divine affection in all creation. The love of the Sons in their ministry to the races is superb, but the devotion of an Adjuster to the individual is touchingly sublime, divinely Fatherlike.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb5\highlight5 4 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93All miracles mean life, and God is the Giver of life. His Voice will direct you very specifically. You will be told all you need to know.\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0  The Thought Adjuster is God living within us. Jesus took years to perfect his communication with his Adjuster. This Course is his summary of what he learned during his life in the flesh. That is why I believe these two books compliment each other so perfectly. We can see from the account of Jesus life in the UB how he accomplished what he is teaching us in the Course. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 110:1.1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85.And indirectly and unrecognized the Adjuster is constantly communicating with the human subject, especially during those sublime experiences of the worshipful contact of mind with spirit in the superconsciousness.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 110:1.2 These heavenly helpers are dedicated to the stupendous task of guiding you safely inward and upward to the celestial haven of happiness. These tireless toilers are consecrated to the future personification of the triumph of divine truth in your life everlasting. They are the watchful workers who pilot the God-conscious human mind away from the shoals of evil while expertly guiding the evolving soul of man toward the divine harbors of perfection on far-distant and eternal shores. The Adjusters are loving leaders, your safe and sure guides through the dark and uncertain mazes of your short earthly career; they are the patient teachers who so constantly urge their subjects forward in the paths of progressive perfection. They are the careful custodians of the sublime values of creature character. I wish you could love them more, co-operate with them more fully, and cherish them more affectionately.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0\cb5\highlight5 5 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Miracles are habits and should be involuntary. They should not be under conscious control. Consciously selected miracles can be misguided.\u8221\'94}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0  Many religious people to this day try to perform miracles at will. This miracle principal is a good example of why this course is inspired by Jesus. The apostles tried to imitate Jesus healing approach. But they failed miserably to heal a young boy. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 158:4.6 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8230\'85.."If it has been given you to do these works, I pray that you will speak those words which will deliver my child from this bondage." Then Simon stepped forward and, placing his hand on the head of the child, looked directly into his eyes and commanded: "Come out of him, you unclean spirit; in the name of Jesus obey me." But the lad had only a more violent fit, while the scribes mocked the apostles in derision, and the disappointed believers suffered the taunts of these unfriendly critics.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 After Simons defeat Jesus showed up and heard the story and this was his reply: \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93"O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I bear with you? How long shall I be with you? How long ere you learn that the works of faith come not forth at the bidding of doubting unbelief?" Then Jesus went on to heal the boy. Jesus knew the apostles were seeking preferred honor in Jesus\u8217\'92s kingdom. The apostles were certainly misguided. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Later in the next section of the UB Jesus gave the apostles a short lecture on how they were misguided. I won\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t list the whole section here but it is worth reading in relation to this miracle principal. As part of Jesus\u8217\'92s explanation he said this \u8220\'93How long will it take you to learn that you cannot time-shorten the course of established natural phenomena except when such things are in accordance with the Father\u8217\'92s will? nor can you do spiritual work in the absence of spiritual power. And you can do neither of these, even when their potential is present, without the existence of that third and essential human factor, the personal experience of the possession of living faith.\u8221\'94 What I found most interesting about this quote was Jesus own reference to \u8220\'93time-shorten\u8221\'94 in reference to their attempt to heal the boy. The Course and UB both use that language in relation to miracles. If you like you can use this link to read the whole section.}
